import glob
import librosa
import pyworld
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from scipy.stats import norm
import IPython.display

def getWaves(gpath: str):
    return [librosa.load(path, sr=16000)[0].astype(np.double) for path in glob.glob(gpath)]

def getF0(waves):
    return [pyworld.harvest(w, 16000)[0] for w in waves]

waves = getWaves('jvs_hiho_ver1/jvs002/parallel100/wav24kHz16bit/VOICEACTRESS100_003.wav')
f0, t = pyworld.harvest(waves[0], 16000)
plt.figure(figsize=(25,5))
plt.plot(t, np.ma.log(f0).data)
plt.plot(t, [5 for _ in t])
